<recipe>
<title>
How to Make Granola
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 1 hour
TOTAL TIME: 1 hour 10 minutes
COURSE: Breakfast, Snack
SERVINGS: 8
</details>
<ingredients>
4 cups rolled oats
1 cup shredded coconut
1 cup slivered almonds
1/2 cup pumpkin seeds or sunflower seeds
1/4 cup chia seeds
1/4 cup raw shelled hemp seeds
1/4 cup shelled pistachios
1/2 cup vegetable oil
1/2 cup agave nectar honey, or maple syrup
1/2 cup dried cherries
1/2 cup dried cranberries
3 tablespoons cacao nibs
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 225 F. Line a large, rimmed sheet pan with a silicone baking liner or with parchment paper.
Toss all of the granola ingredients together in a large bowl.
Spread into an even layer on the prepared baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, and let cool to room temperature.
Break apart, and store in a covered container.
</instructions>
</recipe>
